病歷號碼 : 0002018266       科    別 : 精神科       檢查日期 : 20200708
病患姓名 : 詹銘海       性    別 : 男       檢查時間 : 124815
年    齡 : 64       醫囑醫師 : 王志嘉
Brain with MRA +DWI without contrast
IMPRESSION F31.2 Bipolar disorder, current episode manic severe with 
psychotic features,   照會資料 first psychosis,

Imaging findings :
MR of brain without contrast enhancement shows: 
> Linear T1/FLAIR hyperintensity along both occipital lobes by midline. 
Suspected SAH. 
> No diffusion restriction lesion is detected.
> No obvious space taking lesion in CSF space and brain parenchyma.
> Mild ventricular dilatation and widening of cortical sulci and Sylvian 
fissures.
> T2 hyperintense foci in the periventricular white matter of bilateral 
cerebral hemispheres.
> Encephalomalacia at both cerebellar hemispheres.
> Rhinitis.
> MRA shows luminal stenosis at the left ACA and bilateral PCAs. 
> A 4.5-cm mass lesion between the right ICA and ECA. Suggest further 
study.

Impression :
1. Linear T1/FLAIR hyperintensity along both occipital lobes by midline. 
Suspected SAH.
2. Mild brain atrophy with leukoaraiosis.
3. Encephalomalacia at both cerebellar hemispheres.
4. A 4.5-cm mass lesion between the right ICA and ECA. Suggest further 
study.
5. MRA shows luminal stenosis at the left ACA and bilateral PCAs.

Brain with MRA +DWI without contrast
IMPRESSION G40.89 Other seizures,   照會資料 g,

with T1/FLAIR hyperintensity along gyrus. Probable prior lamellar 
necrosis or hemorrhagic transformation.
> No diffusion restriction lesion is detected.
> No obvious space taking lesion in CSF space and brain parenchyma.
> No obvious intracranial hemorrhage.
> Ventricular dilatation and widening of cortical sulci and Sylvian

Impression :

with T1/FLAIR hyperintensity along gyrus. Probable prior lamellar 
necrosis or hemorrhagic transformation.
2. Brain atrophy with leukoaraiosis.
3. MRA shows occlusion of the inferior division of the left MCA.

病歷號碼 : 0002019544       科    別 : 神經內科       檢查日期 : 20200710
病患姓名 : 程秀麗       性    別 : 女       檢查時間 : 104326
年    齡 : 71       醫囑醫師 : 鄭盟儒
Brain with MRA +DWI without contrast
IMPRESSION I67.9 Cerebrovascular disease, unspecified,   照會資料 .,

Imaging findings :
MRI of the head (brain) without IV contrast enhancement shows:
1. confluent and symmetric periventricular white matter hyperintensity 
(WMH) with high SI on DWI and low SI on ADC map at the periphery of WMH 
in the bil. cerebral hemispheres. 
2. cortical brain atrophy with prominent sulci and fissures, and mild 
ventriculomegaly.
3. old lacunes at the bil. thalami and right centrum semiovale. 
4. fetal origin of the left posterior cerebral artery (PCA) from the left 
posterior communicating artery (PComA) with absence of the P1 segment, 
and multifocal stenosis at the P2 segment. 
5. no evidence of dural sinus thrombosis.
6. hyperostosis frontalis interna; r/o left chronic maxillary sinusitis 
and chronic otitis media.  
7. degenerative spinal and disk disease, visible cervical spine, with 
spinal stenosis and cord compression, C3-4 level; block vertebra, C2-3 
level. 

Impression :
white matter disease, bil. cerebral hemispheres, r/o progressive 
multifocal leukoencephalopathy (PML)? 
cortical brain atrophy with mild ventriculomegaly. 
old lacunes, bil. thalami and right centrum semiovale. 
left fetal PCA with multifocal stenosis, P2 segment. 
hyperostosis frontalis interna; r/o left chronic maxillary sinusitis and 
chronic otitis media.  
degenerative spinal and disk disease, visible cervical spine, with spinal 
stenosis and cord compression, C3-4 level; block vertebra, C2-3 level.

Brain with MRA +DWI without contrast
IMPRESSION D43.2 Neoplasm of uncertain behavior of brain, unspecified,   
照會資料  ,.,

Imaging findings :
MRI of the head (brain) without IV contrast enhancement shows:
1. suboptimal study due to some motion artifacts. 
2. a 4.8-cm lobulated mass of mixed SI on all sequences at the right 
frontal lobe with marked perifocal edema and leftward subfalcine 
herniation, and increase in size as comparison with prior study on 
2019/11/12. 
3. mild asymmetric ventriculomegaly. 
4. no evidence of dural sinus thrombosis.
5. r/o bil. chronic paranasal sinusitis; s/p radical mastoidectomy on 
left side. 
6. degenerative spinal and disk disease, visible cervical spine, with 
spinal stenosis and cord compression, C3-4 and C4-5 levels. 

Impression :
malignant brain tumor, right frontal lobe, r/o metastasis or glioma, with 
marked leftward subfalcine herniation, in progression. 
mild asymmetric ventriculomegaly. 
r/o bil. chronic paranasal sinusitis; s/p radical mastoidectomy, left. 
degenerative spinal and disk disease, visible cervical spine, with spinal 
stenosis and cord compression, C3-4 and C4-5 levels.

病患姓名 : 徐紫櫻       性    別 : 女       檢查時間 : 125849
年    齡 : 57       醫囑醫師 : 陳建銘
Brain with MRA +DWI with contrast
C.C. CxR  less pleural effusion,CxR  less pleural effusion,CxR  less 
pleural effusion, , , ,Demrat

Imaging findings :
MRI of the head (brain) without/with IV contrast enhancement shows:
1. localized magnetic susceptibility artifact(s) at the left suprasellar 
and frontotemporal areas. 
2. mild cortical brain atrophy with prominent sulci and fissures, and 
slight dilated ventricles.
3. some tiny foci of high SI on T2WI in the bil. periventricular deep 
white matter, suggestive of leukoaraiosis.
4. varying-sized nodules of mild enhancement scattered at the bil. 
cerebral hemispheres with decrease in size and number as comparison with 
prior study on 2020/04/24. 
5. susp. fetal origin of the right posterior cerebral artery (PCA) from 
the right posterior communicating artery (PComA) with absence of the P1 
segment. 
6. no evidence of dural sinus thrombosis.

Impression :
postoperative changes, left suprasellar and frontotemporal areas. 
mild cortical brain atrophy with leukoaraiosis. 
multiple brain metastases, bil. cerebral hemispheres, in regression. 
r/o right fetal PCA.

Brain with MRA +DWI with contrast
C.C. r/o left CN 4 or right CN 6 palsy, r/o MG, r/o left midbrain 
lesion.,r/o left CN 4 or right C

Imaging findings :
MRI of the head (brain) without/with IV contrast enhancement shows:
1. no evidence of abnormal bright SI on DWI.
2. mild cortical brain atrophy with prominent sulci and fissures, and 
ventriculomegaly.
3. some tiny foci of high SI on T2WI in the bil. periventricular deep 
white matter, suggestive of leukoaraiosis.
4. hypoplasia of the right vertebral artery (VA); fetal origin of the 
bil. posterior cerebral arteries (PCAs) from the bil. posterior 
communicating arteries (PComAs), and segmental severe stenosis at the P2
-3 segments of bil. PCAs.  
5. no evidence of dural sinus thrombosis.
6. r/o bil. chronic maxillary sinusitis. 
7. degenerative spinal and disk disease, cervical spine, with mild spinal 
stenosis and cord compression, C3-4 and C4-5 levels. 

Impression :
mild cortical brain atrophy with ventriculomegaly and leukoaraiosis. 
right VA hypoplasia; bil. fetal PCAs with segmental severe stenosis, P2-3
segments. 
r/o bil. chronic maxillary sinusitis. 
degenerative spinal and disk disease, cervical spine, with mild spinal 
stenosis and cord compression, C3-4 and C4-5 levels.
